The paper deals with concurrent programming and synchronization mechanisms, which are typically studied in the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Operating Systems (cs.OS) sub-categories. The paper also presents a methodology for checking shared memory access, which falls under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper defines an abstract model of resource access and provides a formal semantics, which are topics studied in the Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-categories.
